    "en": {
      "title": "Asia Cup: Sri Lanka beat Afghanistan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka won the Super 4 round match against Afghanistan in Sharjah, UAE today.",
        "Sri Lanka's captain Dasun Shanaka, who won the toss of the match, announced that his team will field first.",
        "Afghanistan, who batted first, scored 175 runs for the loss of 6 wickets in 20 overs with Rahmanullah Gurbaz's 84 (45), Ibrahim Zadran's 40 (38), Najibullah Zadran's 17 (10), Rashid Khan's 09 (07). In bowling, Dilshan Madhushanka had figures of 2/37 [4], Mahesh Dikshana 1/29 [4], Asitha Fernando 1/34 [4], Vanidu Hazaranga 0/23 [4].",
        "In reply, Sri Lanka were bowled out for 176 runs, with Kusal Mendis getting off to a fast start through Padum Nisanga, before Mendis fell to Naveen-ul-Haq for 36 (19). In no time, Nisanga was bowled by Mujeeb ur Rahman for 35 (28) runs, while Charit Azalanga and Shanaka fell to captain Mohammad Nabi and Mujeeb at intervals.",
        "Later, Danushka Gunathilaka, who moved towards victory, scored 33 (20) runs to Rashid Khan, while Banuka Rajapaksa fell to Naveen with 31 (14) runs, Hazaranga's unbeaten 16 (09) and Samika Karunaratne's unbeaten 05 (02), Sri Lanka won by 6 wickets in 19.1 overs."
      ],
